1   The load balancer is configured as a cluster so that if one fails, the other takes over:
Configuring a load balancer as a cluster is a common practice to ensure high availability and fault tolerance. In such a configuration, multiple load balancer instances are set up as a cluster, and they work together to distribute incoming traffic across a group of servers or backend resources.